	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've spent a huge amount of time studying the first five quests (up to Obsidian Coldain Insignia Ring) and trying all kinds of stuff.  If you want any tips that I don't give here, come onto Torvonnilous server, name is Simaton.  Send me a tell.  I've soloed through the first five quests several times as a lvl 48 ranger.  First quest is easy with snare and panic animal and a decent tailoring skill (was trivial for me at 40 skill).  2nd quest can be soloed VERY easily.  HARMONY!  WOOT!  Just follow Boridain Glacierbane as he approaches the giant city.  When he is starting to get near, harmony Boridain while he is near you (so that the harmony hits you too and you will be able to see when Boridain's harmony is about to run out).  Then run ahead and harmony each of the giants in front of the giant for if needed.  Then harmony the one giant at the ulthorks where Boridain stops next (Make sure you keep Boridain himself harmonied or he will aggro on the mobs), and then harmony the giants in front of the city for the 2nd time when he goes back.  Then use snare and panic animal on the rabid kodiak and *viola*  you've just soloed the whole 2nd quest and didn't lose a hp, if you're good.  Third quest is easy too, snare and panic animal on walrusses until you get HQ pelt, find a skinning stone sitting on the qround, fear kite rhinos till you get a horn (not too rare).  Fourth quest:  This one is tricky to solo.  Trigger the quest by saying &quot;help&quot; to Tain.  Watch for the gaints that will pop from straight EAST of you, from over the hill.  Pull them and run like all get out (have sow up or die).  Use F9 to adjust screens as you run, and target a giant that is not the named giant.  When just out of casting range, stop and start clicking on snare button.  Repeat till all are snared except names one.  The others will get left behind and depop.  Kite the named one.  Some rangers think this takes a long time, but there ARE tricks....  Tricks to kill a giant NPC with a ton of HP faster than a druid can dot them to death.  But I won't go into that now, unless you wanna send me a tell on Torv.  Anyways.... kite him till he's dead.  Tain may be depopped or dead by now, no biggie, when he pops again, trigger the quest and turn in the letter from Garadain and then the Elixer from the named giant FAST before they kill you and get outa there with the smithy hammer.  Give that with ring to Garadain and you're set.  Soloing the 5th ring I just figured out today.  Omg, I wasted so many invasion plans figuring out a way to solo this.  It's so simple it's STUPID!  Turn in the plans to lookout.  IMMEDIATELY run and target (why do I keep forgetting NPC names?) the named SK orc.  Oh yeah, Scarbrow.  Harmony him quick (don't interrupt your casting though, I hate that).   Then pull with arrow.  Viola!  You have only Scarbrow alone, nothing else.  Take him out and kite him (send me a tell online if you wanna know the FAST way to kite him down in minutes, arrow kiting and dot kiting are way slow, but they will work if you're desperate.  Hard to kite a SK though).  A few details to brush up on... Lessee...  Scarbrow will HT you right when you pull with arrow.  Ouch.  No biggie if you're good.  Kite him.  Oh, and the places to kite the named giant and scarbrow...  May be several place, but the one that I LOVE is to head straight south from bridge to Iceclad, follow the border of the east zone cliff until you reach the south &quot;border&quot; (cliff) of the zone, and head east towards Korrigain and walrusses.  There are almost never any mobs there ever.  Kite your heart out.  For Scarbrow, take him east to the bridge without snaring him (or it'll take forever) and then the same route till you get to the southern edge of the map, then snare and kite.  I'm just starting the 6th ring and working on a way to solo it just like all the others.  I may post it when I find a way to solo it... but only if I remember.  I think the trick I use to kite scarbrow and the named giant will probably work on the other two NPCs I gotta kill for the 6th ring.  We'll see, I haven't tested it yet.  Have fun, and luck with your quests.  -Simaton
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
